annotationA: Fructose-bisphosphate aldolase; May take part in developmental stage-specific or tissue -specific sugar-phosphate metabolisms. Protein acts on two substrates fructose 1,6-bisphosphate and fructose 1-phosphate (like other class I aldolases)
annotationB: ATP binding; phosphoglycerate kinase activity. It is involved in the biological process described with: glycolytic process; myoblast fusion; muscle cell cellular homeostasis; synaptic transmission; somatic muscle development; phosphorylation
